ia.%20Officials%20say%20it's%20the%20state's%20first%20'locally%20acquired'%20case%20in%2040%20years.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221867%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20mosquito%20bites%20skin.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64e25905b698ac0019dd9215%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221398%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20mosquito%20bites%20skin.%3Cp%3ESlowmotiongli%2FGetty%20Images.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMaryland%20detected%20a%20locally%20acquired%20case%20of%20malaria%2C%20the%20first%20in%20over%2040%20years%2C%20health%20officials%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIt%20comes%20after%20similar%20cases%20were%20reported%20earlier%20this%20summer%20in%20Florida%20and%20Texas.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHealth%20officials%20maintain%20there%20is%20an%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20low%26quot%3B%20risk%20of%20locally%20contracting%20malaria%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESomeone%20in%20Maryland%20contracted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fmalaria-in-us-expert-tips-to-avoid-getting-sick-2023-6%5C%22%3Emalaria%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20officials%20are%20scratching%20their%20heads%20as%20they%20grapple%20with%20the%20state's%20first%20local%20case%20of%20the%20disease%20in%20four%20decades.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Maryland%20Department%20of%20Health%20confirmed%20the%20case%20on%20Friday%2C%20saying%20the%20individual%20lives%20in%20the%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%2C%20region%20and%20had%20not%20recently%20traveled%20internationally%20%E2%80%93%20a%20common%20flag%20for%20malaria%20cases.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMalaria%20was%20once%20common%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20including%20in%20Maryland%2C%20but%20we%20have%20not%20seen%20a%20case%20in%20Maryland%20that%20was%20not%20related%20to%20travel%20in%20over%2040%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Laura%20Herrera%20Scott%2C%20secretary%20of%20the%20state%20Department%20of%20Heath%2C%20said%20in%20