%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F7%2F11%2Fworld-population-day-what-will-the-world-look-like-in-2050%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENigeria%20had%20fewer%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%2080%20million%20people%20and%20was%20outside%20the%20world's%2010%20most%20populous%20countries.%20In%20the%2041%20years%20since%2C%20Nigeria's%20population%20has%20nearly%20tripled%20to%20225%20million%2C%20moving%20up%20to%20sixth%20on%20the%20list.%20And%20that%20is%20not%20expected%20to%20slow%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fdevelopment%2Fdesa%2Fpd%2Fsites%2Fwww.un.org.development.desa.pd%2Ffiles%2Fwpp2022_summary_of_results.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20recent%20UN%20projections%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Nigeria%20will%20nearly%20double%20its%20population%20again%20by%202050%20to%20an%20estimated%20377%20million.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20the%20country%20will%20leap-frog%20Pakistan%20and%20Indonesia%20and%20end%20up%20in%20a%20virtual%20tie%20with%20the%20US%20as%20the%20third%20most%20populous%20country%20in%20the%20world.%20That's%20incredible%20for%20a%20country%20that%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmapfight.xyz%2Fcompare%2Fng-vs-texas%2F%5C%22%3Ejust%20a%20bit%20bigger%20than%20the%20area%20of%20Texas.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221462%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Map%20of%20Texas%20overlaying%20a%20map%20of%20Nigeria.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ad7de494be880019f36a23%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221040%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20outline%20of%20Texas%20overlaying%20a%20map%20of%20Nigeria.%3Cp%3EGoogle%20Maps%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENigeria's%20stunning%20growth%20is%20also%20indicative%20of%20the%20African%20continent.%20According%20to%20the%20UN%20estimates%2C%20five%20of%20the%20eight%20countries%20expected%20to%20make%20up%20half%20of%20the%20world's%20population%20growth%20over%20the%20next%2027%20years%20are%20in%20Africa.%20In%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.africanews.com%2F2023%2F07%2F10%2Fworld-population-day-populations-in-africa-surge%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20interview%20with%20Africa%20News%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Tighisti%20Amare%2C%20the%20Deputy%20Director%20of%20the%20Africa%20Programme%20Chatham%20House%20in%20London%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20Africa%20is%20the%20fastest-growing%20continent%20and%20the%20youngest%2C%20noting%20that%2070%25%20of%20the%20population%20is%20under%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20population%20growth%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20partly%20explained%20by%20improvement%20in%20level%20and%20access%20to%20public%20health%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.africanews.com%2F2023%2F07%2F10%2Fworld-population-day-populations-in-africa-surge%2F%5C%22%3EAmare%20said%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThat%20has%20led%20to%20decrease%20in%20child%20mortality.%20And%20that%20by%20itself%20is%20good%20news.%20And%20the%20other%20good%20news%20is%20that%20also%20by%20having%20a%20young%20population%2C%20most%20African%20nations%20do%20not%20have%20the%20burden%20of%20a%20large%20elderly%20population%20that%20relies%20on%20taxes%20and%20pensions%2C%20which%20can%20be%20a%20strain%20on%20the%20economy%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20noted%20that%20because%20of%20such%20a%20young%20population%2C%20countries%20like%20Nigeria%20are%20producing%20more%20workers%20in%20the%20tech%20industry%2C%20increasing%20the%20possibility%20that%20the%20solutions%20for%20issues%20that%20impact%20Africa%2C%20such%20as%20climate%20change%2C%20are%20developed%20domestically.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20positives%2C%20there%20are%20also%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unfpa.org%2Fresources%2Fpopulation-and-development-africa%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplenty%20of%20dev