xtremist%20groups%2C%20including%20the%20so-called%20%E2%80%9CIslamic%20State%2C%E2%80%9D%20have%20claimed%20responsibility%20for%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fpakistan-blast-near-mosque-in-peshawar-leaves-dozens-dead%2Fa-64552197%5C%22%3Eseveral%20attacks%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fwhy-suicide-attacks-are-on-the-rise-in-pakistan%2Fa-66407341%5C%22%3Emajor%20explosion%20at%20a%20political%20gathering%20in%20Khyber%20Pakhtunkhwa%3C%2Fa%3E%20organised%20by%20a%20religious%20faction%20last%20month%20resulted%20in%20the%20deaths%20of%2045%20individuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fpakistan-11-laborers-killed-in-bomb-blast%2Fa-66580598%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20DW.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Farticle%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fsection%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692531550000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F24215513%2F6483091829_b0a9599ab5_k.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fpakistan-11-labourers-killed-in-suspected-militant-attack%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20security%20and%20police%20officials%2C%20a%20suspected%20improvised%20explosive%20device%20(IED)%20detonated%20beneath%20a%20truck%20transporting%20workers%20to%20an%20army%20construction%20site%20in%20Waziristan%2C%20situated%20in%20Khyber%20Pakhtunkhwa%20province.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fpakistan-11-labourers-killed-in-suspected-militant-attack%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22We20%20Summit%20Issues%20Declaration%20Calling%20for%20Solidarity%2C%20Unity%20Among%20Democratic%20Forces%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F20165720%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-08-20-at-10.33.37.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20We20%20Summit%20%E2%80%93%20where%20parliamentarians%2C%20activists%20and%20academics%20were%20scheduled%20to%20speak%20%E2%80%93%20issued%20a%20declaration%20on%20Sunday%20(August%2020)%20titled%20%E2%80%98People%20and%20Nature%20over%20Profits%20for%20a%20Just%2C%20Inclusive%2C%20Transparent%20and%20Equitable%20Future%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20three-day%20summit%20started%20off%20without%20a%20hitch%20on%20Friday%2C%20but%20was%20disrupted%20by%20the%20police%20on%20Saturday.%20While%20the%20event%20was%20able%20to%20continue%20on%20Saturday%20after%20the%20organisers%20and%20speakers%20stood%20their%20ground%2C%20Sunday%E2%80%99s%20sessions%20had%20to%20be%20cancelled%20after%20the%20police%20refused%20permission%20for%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20declaration%20adopted%20on%20Sunday%20called%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20solidarity%20and%20unity%20among%20all%20democratic%20forces%2C%20peoples%E2%80%99%20movements%2C%20civil%20society%20organizations%2C%20human%20rights%20defenders%20and%20progressive%20individuals%20to%20demand%20robust%20South-South%20cooperation%2C%20and%20a%20just%2C%20inclusive%2C%20transparent%20and%20equitable%20future%20for%20people%20all%20over%20the%20world%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20700%20delegates%20from%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20country%2C%20representing%20people%E2%80%99s%20movements%2C%20trade%20unions%20and%20civil%20society%20organisations%2C%20had%20gathered%20for%20the%20event.%20Speakers%20included%20Teesta%20Setalvad%2C%20Medha%20Patkar%2C%20Jayati%20Ghosh%2C%20Manoj%20Jha%2C%20Harsh%20Mander%2C%20Arun%20Kumar%2C%20Brinda%20Karat%2C%20Hannan%20Mollah%2C%20Rajeev%20Gowda%20and%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERead%20the%20full%20text%20of%20the%20declaration%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20This%20declaration%20%E2%80%98%3Cb%3EPeople%20and%20Nature%20over%20Profits%20for%20a%20Just%2C%20Inclusive%2C%20Transparent%20and%20Equitable%20Future%3C%2Fb%3E%E2%80%99%20is%20an%20articulation%20of%20the%20collective%20voices%20of%20the%20participants%20that%20has%20been%20adopted%20unanimously%20at%20the%20We20%20Summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20The%20%3Cb%3EWe20%3A%20A%20Peoples%E2%80%99%20Summit%20on%20G20%2C%3C%2Fb%3E%C2%A0has%20been%20a%20successful%20gathering%20of%20different%20people%E2%80%99s%20movements%2C%20trade%20unions%2C%20civil%20society%20organizations%20and%20concerned%20individuals%20who%20came%20together%20in%20New%20Delhi%20from%2018%20to%2020%20August%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%2018th%20G20%20Leaders%E2%80%99%20Summit%2C%20to%20share%20diverse%20experiences%20and%20knowledge%2C%20and%20demand%20action%20from%20decision-makers%20of%20the%20G20.%20The%20deliberations%20of%20the%20We20%20Summit%C2%A0in%20thematic%20workshops%C2%A0focused%20on%20the%20following%20topics%3A%20(i)%20G20%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20presidency%2C%20(ii)%20Right%20to%20Information%2C%20Digital%20Data%20and%20Surveillance%2C%20(iii)%20Climate%20Change%2C%20Environment%2C%20Biodiversity%20and%20associated%20human%20rights%2C%20(iv)%C2%A0%20global%20finance%2C%20big%20banks%20and%20impact%20on%20the%20people%2C%20(v)%20agriculture%20and%20food%20security%2C%20(vi)%20inequality%2C%20labor%20rights%20and%20social%20protection%2C%20(vii)%20right%20to%20just%2C%20sustainable%2C%20participatory%20and%20inclusive%20city%2C%20(viii)%20fascism%20and%20marginalization%2C%20and%20(ix)%20rights%20of%20natural%20resource-dependent%20communities.%20The%20We20%20Summit%20was%20attended%20by%20over%20500%20people%20from%20over%20eighteen%20states%20of%20India%20who%20represented%20the%20working%20class%2C%20Dalits%2C%20Adivasis%2C%20persons%20with%20disabilities%2C%20ethnic%20and%20religious%20minority%20communities%2C%20farmers%2C%20fisherpeople%2C%20forest%20workers%2C%20hawkers%2C%20artisans%2C%20unorganized%20workers%2C%20academicians%2C%20and%20members%20of%20the%20civil%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.%20India%20is%20hosting%20the%2018th%20G20%20Leaders%E2%80%99%20Summit%20on%209%20and10%20September%202023%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20We%2C%20the%20people%2C%20assert%20that%20the%20G20%2C%20since%20its%20inception%2C%20has%20been%20an%20elite%20club%20in%20terms%20of%20its%20membership%20and%20actions.%20This%20informal%20group%20of%20rich%20and%20%E2%80%98emerging%20market%20economies%E2%80%99%20has%20taken%20policy%20decisions%20to%20serve%20the%20economic%20and%20political%20interests%20of%20corporations%2C%20advanced%20the%20neoliberal%20agenda%20promoted%20by%20international%20institutions%20such%20as%20the%20World%20Bank%2C%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20(IMF)%2C%20the%20Asian%20Development%20Bank%20(ADB)%20and%20the%20WTO%2C%20and%20has%20repeatedly%20failed%20to%20address%20the%20pressing%20concerns%20of%20people.%20These%20include%20economic%2C%20social%20and%20ecological%20injustice%3B%20inequality%3B%20agrarian%2C%20food%20and%20livelihood%20crises%3B%20debt%20distress%3B%20accelerating%20climate%20change%3B%20and%20human%20rights%20violations%20and%20democratic%20backsliding.%20We%2C%20the%20people%2C%20assert%20that%20the%20G20%20needs%20to%20urgently%20acknowledge%20people%E2%80%99s%20voices%20and%20priorities%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20those%20most%20vulnerable%20to%2C%20and%20affected%20by%2C%20inequality%20and%20crises%20%E2%80%93%20and%20respond%20appropriately%20by%20putting%20people%20and%20nature%20over%20profits%20for%20a%20just%2C%20inclusive%2C%20transparent%20and%20equitable%20financial%20and%20development%20system%20and%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E4.%20The%20We20%20Summit%20shook%20the%20government%20as%20was%20evident%20from%20the%20Delhi%20police%E2%80%99s%20attempt%20to%20suppress%20peoples%E2%80%99%20voices%20by%20barricading%20the%20venue%20on%20the%20second%20day%20to%20stop%20the%20entry%20of%20delegates%20who%20came%20to%20attend%20the%20workshops.%20The%20police%20also%20denied%20permission%20to%20hold%20the%20event%20on%20the%20third%20day.%20We%20strongly%20protest%20against%20the%20arbitrary%20action%20of%20the%20police%20to%20prevent%20people%20from%20exercising%20their%20democratic%20right%20to%20assemble%20peacefully%20and%20freely%20express%20their%20opinions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E5.%20The%20G20%20events%20in%20India%20are%20being%20organized%20at%20a%20time%20when%20we%20are%20going%20through%20a%20phase%20of%20rising%20inequalities%2C%20systematic%20erosion%20of%20the%20rights%20of%20workers%2C%20farmers%2C%20fishers%2C%20Dalits%20and%20Adivasis%2C%20skyrocketing%20food%20and%20energy%20prices%2C%20extreme%20weather%20events%20engendered%20by%20climate%20crisis%2C%20widespread%20ecological%20destruction%2C%20inter-faith%20and%20inter-religious%20conflicts%2C%20increased%20violence%20against%20women%20and%20gender%20diverse%20persons%2C%20and%20shrinking%20democratic%20spaces.%20We%20bear%20witness%20that%20the%20preparations%20for%20the%20G20%20mega-events%20in%20New%20Delhi%20and%20in%20many%20other%20cities%20across%20India%20have%20led%20to%20gross%20violations%20of%20human%20rights%20of%20thousands%20of%20urban%20poor%20and%20marginalized%20communities%2C%20who%20have%20been%20forcibly%20evicted%20from%20their%20homes%20and%20deprived%20of%20their%20livelihoods%20without%20due%20process%2C%20compensation%20or%20proper%20rehabilitation.%20As%20documented%20in%20a%20public%20hearing%20report%20released%20on%2013%20July%202023%2C%20the%20forced%20evictions%20and%20demolition%20drives%20carried%20out%20by%20state%20agencies%20were%20done%20in%20the%20name%20of%20beautification%2C%20protection%20of%20monuments%20and%20other%20similar%20flimsy%20pretexts.%20We%20strongly%20deplore%20the%20crackdown%20on%20the%20poor%20and%20marginalized%20people%20across%20the%20country%20and%20demand%20participatory%20rehabilitation%20and%20adequate%20compensation%20for%20those%20who%20lost%20their%20livelihoods%20for%20the%20arrangement%20of%20the%20G20%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E6.%20We%20are%20also%20severely%20critical%20of%20the%20use%20of%20crores%20of%20public%20money%20spent%20on%20advertisements%20ostensibly%20to%20promote%20India%E2%80%99s%20presidency%20at%20a%20time%20when%20food%20and%20fuel%20prices%20are%20skyrocketing%2C%20heat%20waves%20and%20flash%20floods%20are%20killing%20people%20and%20devastating%20entire%20communities%2C%20and%20democratic%20spaces%20are%20declining.%20Evicting%20the%20poor%2C%20hiding%20working%20class%20settlements%20behind%20high%20curtains%20and%20spending%20public%20money%20for%20political%20gains%20explicitly%20contradict%20India%E2%80%99s%20much-cherished%20%E2%80%98Mother%20of%20Democracy%E2%80%99%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E7.%20We%20call%20for%20an%20overhaul%20of%20the%20international%20financial%20architecture.%20International%20Financial%20Institutions%20(IFIs)%20such%20as%20the%20World%20Bank%2C%20the%20IMF%2C%20the%20ADB%20and%20the%20Asian%20Infrastructure%20Investment%20Bank%20(AIIB)%20are%20controlled%20by%20former%20colonial%20powers%20and%20emerging%20economies%20with%20imperialist%20interests%20and%20have%20no%20role%20in%20democratic%20polity.%20The%20billions%20of%20dollars%20of%20investments%20by%20the%20IFIs%20in%20critical%20sectors%20such%20as%20energy%2C%20urban%20infrastructure%2C%20transport%2C%20and%20climate%20action%20have%20had%20devastating%20consequences%20for%20the%20lives%20and%20livelihood%20of%20peoples.%20Such%20investments%2C%20as%20we%20have%20seen%20in%20multiple%20mega-projects%20such%20as%20the%20Tata%20Mundra%20Power%20Project%20or%20the%20Amravati%20Capital%20City%20Project%20or%20the%20Bharatmala%20and%20the%20Sagarmala%20projects%2C%20have%20resulted%20in%20corporate%20land%20and%20territory%20grabs%2C%20displacement%20of%20local%20communities%2C%20commodification%20and%20privatisation%20of%20natural%20resources%2C%20environmental%20degradation%2C%20violation%20of%20labor%2C%20fishers%20and%20farmers%20rights%2C%20and%20protecting%20private%20capital%20investments%20against%20economic%20risk%20with%20public%20money.%20Further%2C%20the%20IFIs%20continue%20to%20lobby%20with%20elected%20governments%20to%20bring%20anti-people%20laws%20and%20policies%20(such%20as%20the%20FRDI%20Bill%202017%20or%20the%20three%20farm%20laws%20or%20high%20banking%20charges)%2C%20commodify%20and%20financialize%20land%20and%20essential%20services%2C%20control%20food%20production%20systems%2C%20and%20finance%20projects%20without%20adequate%20environmental%20and%20social%20safeguards.%20Instead%20of%20rectifying%20global%20power%20imbalances%20in%20economic%20governance%2C%20the%20G20%20reforms%20of%20IFIs%20have%20pushed%20for%20increased%20private%20sector%20investments%20and%20foreign%20direct%20investments%20(FDI).%20Specifically%20in%20key%20areas%20such%20as%20agriculture%2C%20health%20and%20education%2C%20this%20will%20have%20a%20negative%20impact%20on%20people%E2%80%99s%20lives%20and%20the%20environment%20through%20privatisation%20and%20commercialisation%20of%20essential%20services.%20It%20will%20also%20destabilise%20constitutionally%20mandated%20democratic%20governance%20and%20national%20security%20of%20individual%20countries.%20We%20demand%20more%20public%20spending%20on%20health%2C%20education%2C%20agriculture%20and%20all%20essential%20services%2C%20and%20reject%20financial%20austerity%20measures%20as%20solutions%20to%20the%20renewed%20debt%20crisis%20in%20many%20South%20countries.%20We%20also%20make%20a%20call%20for%20South-South%20cooperation%20to%20revamp%20the%20international%20financial%20system%20and%20demand%20that%20the%20elected%20governments%20of%20the%20countries%20of%20the%20global%20South%20commit%20to%20the%20peoples%E2%80%99%20interests%20instead%20of%20advancing%20the%20same%20of%20the%20corporations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E8.%20In%20a%20world%20marred%20by%20multiple%2C%20intersecting%20crises%20triggered%20by%20the%20unbridled%20finance%20capital%20and%20the%20tendency%20of%20global%20capitalism%20to%20extract%20%E2%80%98value%E2%80%99%20from%20every%20crisis%2C%20resolution%20of%20the%20debt%20distress%20of%20low%20and%20middle%20income%20countries%20(LMICs)%20is%20a%20top%20agenda%20of%20the%20G20.%20However%2C%20past%20solutions%20such%20as%20the%20Debt%20Service%20Suspension%20Initiative%20have%20failed%20to%20address%20the%20debt%20crisis%20by%20not%20being%20able%20to%20engage%20private%20creditors%20in%20resolving%20the%20same%20and%2C%20instead%2C%20creating%20conditions%20for%20more%20debt-creating%20finance.%20We%20reject%20the%20G20%E2%80%99s%20zeal%20to%20push%20for%20profit-oriented%20private%20investments%20in%20the%20LMICs%20and%20flawed%20market-driven%20initiatives%20to%20support%20development%20and%20climate%20action.%20As%20India%20claims%20to%20become%20the%20voice%20of%20the%20global%20South%2C%20the%20demand%20for%20debt%20justice%20for%20the%20LMICs%20must%20be%20a%20priority%20under%20its%20presidency.%20We%20demand%20debt-free%20and%20grant-based%20financing%20to%20support%20the%20appropriate%20developmental%20goals%20and%20ecological%2Fclimate%20action%20in%20the%20developing%20world%2C%20removal%20of%20all%20policy%20conditionality%20to%20finance%2C%20implementation%20of%20transparency%20and%20accountability%20safeguards%2C%20fair%20channeling%20of%20Special%20Drawing%20Rights%20for%20countries%20of%20the%20global%20South%2C%20and%20reparations%20and%20justice%20from%20the%20rich%20countries%20of%20the%20global%20North%20for%20the%20immense%20past%20and%20continuing%20ecological%20and%20other%20forms%20of%20debt%20they%20owe%20to%20the%20global%20South.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E9.%20The%20false%20market-based%20solutions%20to%20the%20climate%20crises%20proposed%20by%20the%20G20%20and%20similar%20fora%20have%20resulted%20in%20financialisation%20of%20nature%20and%20deprivation%20of%20natural%20resource-dependent%20communities%2C%20and%20greater%20debt%20distress.%20We%20demand%20immediate%20action%20to%20protect%20the%20environment%20and%20biodiversity%20through%20increased%20debt-free%20climate%20finance%20and%20cancellation%20of%20existing%20debts%2C%20phasing%20out%20of%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20an%20end%20to%20funding%20plastic%20production%20infrastructures%20and%20waste-to-energy%20plants%2C%20reducing%20emissions%20to%20real%20zero%20and%20not%20net%20zero%2C%20advancing%20sustainable%20and%20climate-resilient%20agroecological%20systems%2C%20significant%20public%20outlays%20for%20adaptation%20and%20mitigation%20by%20communities%20already%20being%20severely%20impacted%2C%20recognising%20the%20collective%20governance%20and%20management%20rights%20of%20nature-dependent%20communities%2C%20and%20increased%20public%20spending%20towards%20such%20communities%20to%20save%20our%20water%2C%20forests%2C%20land%20and%20air%20(%3Ci%3Ejal%2C%20jangal%2C%20zameen%2C%20aur%20hawa%3C%2Fi%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E10.%20We%20reject%20corporate%20capital%E2%80%99s%20capture%20of%20global%20food%20governance%20through%20the%20Agreement%20on%20Agriculture%20in%20the%20WTO%2C%20and%20emerging%20bilateral%20and%20multilateral%20trade%20agreements.%20Agricultural%20sustainability%20and%20food%20security%20are%20burning%20issues%20today%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20disruptions%20in%20food%20supply%20chains%20because%20of%20globalised%20trade%20in%20food%20and%20agriculture.%20The%20impacts%20of%20extreme%20weather%20events%20on%20agriculture%20and%20the%20IFI%E2%80%99s%20stress%20on%20agribusiness-driven%20agriculture%20have%20led%20to%20hunger%2C%20malnutrition%20and%20food%20insecurity.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20three%20farm%20laws%20introduced%20in%202020%20by%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20were%20a%20direct%20consequence%20of%20the%20policies%20promoted%20by%20the%20World%20Bank%2C%20the%20IMF%20and%20the%20WTO%20to%20cut%20farm%20and%20food%20subsidies%20and%20destroy%20public%20stockholding%20of%20food%20grains.%20What%20we%20are%20witnessing%20is%20the%20aggressive%20capture%20of%20the%20food%20and%20agriculture%20system%20by%20corporate%20conglomerates.%20We%20demand%20immediate%20coordinated%20actions%20to%20address%20the%20needs%2C%20rights%20and%20demands%20of%20most%20affected%20communities%2C%20make%20the%20public%20distribution%20system%20more%20robust%20and%20inclusive%2C%20and%20call%20for%20a%20radical%20restructuring%20of%20the%20food%20system%20where%20food%20justice%20and%20food%20sovereignty%20are%20central%2C%20and%20where%20respect%20for%C2%A0%20human%20rights%2C%20agroecology%2C%20protecting%20biodiversity%2C%20gender%20justice%20and%20diversity%2C%20youth%20agency%2C%20climate%20justice%2C%20economic%20and%20social%20justice%2C%20and%20safeguarding%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20small%20and%20marginal%20farmers%20and%20natural%20resource-dependent%20communities%2C%20are%20integral%20components.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E11.%20The%20G20%20has%20always%20pushed%20for%20bilateral%20and%20regional%20free%20trade%20agreements%20(FTA)%20to%20serve%20the%20economic%20interests%20of%20wealthy%20countries%2C%20and%20the%20march%20of%20capital.%20India%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20has%20signed%20and%20is%20in%20the%20process%20of%20signing%20FTAs%20with%20Australia%2C%20Canada%2C%20European%20Union%2C%20and%20the%20UK%2C%20the%20terms%20of%20which%20have%20mostly%20been%20kept%20unknown%20to%20the%20people.%20We%20believe%20that%20the%20global%20trade%20system%20is%20broken%20and%20what%20the%20world%20needs%20is%20a%20new%20system%20for%20trade%20based%20on%20economic%20justice%20and%20cooperation%20free%20from%20corporate%20interests%20and%20greed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E12.%20Rising%20inequality%20is%20a%20pressing%20concern%20of%20the%20world%20today.%20As%20noted%20by%20the%20UN%2C%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20has%20exposed%20all%20kinds%20of%20inequalities%2C%20including%20gender%20inequality.%20The%20root%20causes%20for%20rising%20inequalities%20are%20unchecked%20capitalist%20expansion%20supported%20by%20pliant%20nation-states%2C%20tax%20evasion%20and%20avoidance%20by%20powerful%20rich%20actors%2C%20and%20the%20concentration%20of%20financial%20power%20by%20corporations%20to%20safeguard%20the%20interests%20of%20their%20wealthy%20shareholders%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20rights%20of%20working%20classes%2C%20small%20scale%20food%20producers%20and%20of%20nature.%20The%20bargaining%20power%20of%20workers%20has%20been%20systematically%20eroded%20by%20undermining%20trade%20unions%2C%20implementing%20anti-worker%20legislations%20and%20policies%2C%20absence%20of%20social%20protection%20schemes%2C%20and%20introduction%20of%20automation%20in%20workspaces.%20We%20demand%20the%20introduction%20of%20concrete%2C%20time-bound%20targets%20and%20action%20plans%20to%20reduce%20inequality%2C%20end%20the%20accumulation%20of%20extreme%20wealth%20by%20taxing%20the%20top%2C%20create%20more%20jobs%2C%20protect%20the%20rights%20of%20workers%20including%20their%20right%20to%20unionize%20and%20right%20to%20represent%20themselves%20in%20the%20decision-making%20boards%20of%20companies%2C%20eliminate%20the%20gender%20pay%20gap%2C%20make%20multinational%20companies%20follow%20due%20diligence%20in%20line%20with%20the%20UN%20Guiding%20Principles%20on%20Business%20and%20Human%20Rights%2C%20share%20profits%20with%20the%20workers%2C%20protect%20the%20rights%20of%20Dalits%2C%20Adivasis%20and%20marginalized%20communities%2C%20and%20ensure%20gender%20equality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E13.%20We%20strongly%20oppose%20the%20commodification%20and%20privatization%20of%20healthcare%20promoted%20by%20the%20%E2%80%98One%20Health%E2%80%99%20approach.%20The%20pandemic%20has%20also%20exposed%20corporate%20greed%20in%20its%20most%20glaring%20avatar%20and%20the%20G20%20has%20failed%20to%20make%20diagnostics%2C%20treatments%20and%20medicines%20public%20goods%20in%20the%20truest%20sense%20of%20the%20term.%20The%20inability%20of%20the%20G20%20to%20waive%20intellectual%20property%20rights%20of%20corporations%20and%20instead%20promote%20multilateral%20cooperation%20in%20sharing%20treatments%20and%20technologies%20critical%20for%20public%20health%20demonstrate%20the%20elite%2C%20neoliberal%20character%20of%20the%20forum.%20The%20health%20agenda%20of%20the%20G20%20continues%20to%20serve%20the%20interests%20of%20wealthy%20nations%2C%20transnational%20corporations%20and%20philanthropic%20foundations.%20Further%2C%20there%20is%20an%20increasing%20attempt%20to%20invisibilise%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20on%20informal%20workers%2C%20migrant%20laborers%20and%20the%20poor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E14.%20We%20also%20strongly%20protest%20against%20the%20privatisation%20of%20education%20and%20policies%20(such%20as%20the%20New%20Education%20Policy%20of%20India)%20and%20demand%20more%20public%20spending%20in%20education%20infrastructures%20at%20primary%2C%20secondary%20and%20higher%20education%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E15.%20We%20reject%20the%20blue%20economy%20agenda%20of%20the%20G20%20that%20aims%20to%20economically%20exploit%20the%20marine%20ecosystem%20and%20resources%2C%20and%20turn%20conservation%20into%20a%20profitable%20venture.%20The%20push%20for%20attracting%20private%20investments%20in%20the%20name%20of%20protecting%20marine%20life%20and%20sustainable%20tourism%2C%20expansion%20of%20capital-intensive%20large-scale%20aquaculture%2C%20corporatisation%20of%20the%20coastal%20infrastructure%2C%20introduction%20of%20new%20financial%20instruments%20like%20blue%20bonds%2C%20diluting%20environment%20protection%20laws%20to%20benefit%20the%20corporations%2C%20and%20greed%20for%20using%20the%20fossil%20fuel%20oceanscape%20is%20highly%20condemnable.%20We%20have%20no%20doubt%20in%20stating%20that%20the%20blue%20economy%20agenda%20of%20the%20G20%20is%20a%20step%20towards%20extraction%2C%20mining%20and%20grabbing%20of%20marine%20resources%20by%20private%20corporations%20that%20will%20have%20devastating%20consequences%20for%20the%20ocean%20people%2C%20environment%20and%20marine%20ecology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E16.%20We%20are%20deeply%20concerned%20at%20the%20weakening%20of%20environmental%20and%20ecological%20safeguards%20in%20the%20name%20of%20%E2%80%98Be%20Ready%E2%80%99%20or%20for%20the%20single-minded%20pursuit%20of%20economic%20growth.%20In%20India%2C%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20nearly%20every%20environmental%2C%20social%20and%20labour%20laws%20and%20policies%20have%20been%20watered%20down%2C%20rather%20than%20strengthened%20which%20would%20be%20necessary%20in%20the%20context%20of%20national%20and%20global%20ecological%20collapse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E17.%20We%20demand%20that%20scientific%20and%20technological%20research%20must%20be%20more%20people%20centric.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E18.%20We%20strongly%20condemn%20the%20erosion%20of%20democratic%20institutions%20and%20spaces%2C%20the%20attack%20on%20the%20constitutional%20values%2C%20civil%20society%20groups%2C%20human%20rights%20defenders%20and%20academic%20bodies%2C%20the%20use%20of%20digital%20surveillance%20and%20data%20privacy%2C%20the%20dilution%20of%20laws%20related%20to%20right%20to%20information%2C%20criminalisation%20of%20dissent%2C%20unjust%20use%20of%20government%20agencies%20to%20suppress%20peoples%E2%80%99%20voices%2C%20and%20increased%20social%20antagonisms%20and%20communal%20tension%20engineered%20by%20rightwing%20forces.%20In%20India%2C%20we%20have%20witnessed%20the%20creation%20of%20social%20antagonisms%20and%20communal%20tensions%20among%20communities%20in%20Manipur%20and%20Haryana%20just%20days%20before%20the%20G20%20Summit.%20Further%2C%20we%20condemn%20the%20G20%E2%80%99s%20maneuvering%20of%20the%20civil%20society%20voice%20in%20C20%20through%20political%20control%20and%20use%20of%20selected%20religious%20institutions%20and%20pro-private%20capital%20civil%20society%20organisations%20masquerading%20as%20representative%20bodies%20of%20the%20people.%20We%20call%20for%20the%20establishment%20of%20participatory%20and%20plural%20democracy%20and%20equal%20citizenship%2C%20strengthening%20of%20democratic%20institutions%20and%20making%20them%20more%20inclusive%2C%20transparent%20and%20accountable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E19.%20We%20reaffirm%20that%20the%20G20%2C%20is%20an%20exclusive%20elite%20club%20of%20countries%20that%20share%20ideological%20commitment%20to%20neoliberalism%2C%20market%20capitalism%20and%20globalised%20trade%20despite%20their%20continuing%20failure%20to%20deliver%20wellbeing%20to%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20people%20and%20being%20an%20instrument%20of%20legitimisation%20of%20the%20increasing%20authoritarianism%20and%20democratic%20backsliding%20among%20many%20of%20its%20members.%20Decision-making%20and%20governance%20has%20become%20a%20centralized%20exercise%20of%20the%20numerical%20few%2C%20and%20we%20demand%20democratic%20and%20decentralised%20governance%20by%20keeping%20peoples%E2%80%99%20voices%20at%20its%20core.%20Further%2C%20the%20G20%20is%20undermining%20and%20hijacking%20multilateralism%20through%20its%20proposals%20and%20decisions%20on%20global%20economic%20governance%2C%20trade%2C%20finance%2C%20environment%2C%20development%20and%20climate.%20We%20assert%20that%20the%20%E2%80%98one%20earth%2C%20one%20family%2C%20one%20future%E2%80%99%20theme%20of%20the%20G20%20represents%20the%20suppression%20of%20the%20heterogeneity%20and%20diversity%20of%20peoples%E2%80%99%20voices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E20.%20We%20call%20for%20solidarity%20and%20unity%20among%20all%20democratic%20forces%2C%20peoples%E2%80%99%20movements%2C%20civil%20society%20organizations%2C%20human%20rights%20defenders%20and%20progressive%20individuals%20to%20demand%20robust%20South-South%20cooperation%2C%20and%20a%20just%2C%20inclusive%2C%20transparent%20and%20equitable%20future%20for%20people%20all%20over%20the%20world.%20We%20stress%20that%20there%20are%20thousands%20of%20grounded%2C%20community-led%20initiatives%20towards%20genuine%2C%20just%2C%20equitable%20and%20ecologically%20wise%20ways%20of%20meeting%20human%20needs%20available%20across%20the%20G20%20countries%2C%20which%20governments%20and%20others%20can%20learn%20from%20and%20help%20expand%20to%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692530958000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F20165720%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-08-20-at-10.33.37.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwe20-summit-issues-declaration-calling-for-solidarity-unity-among-democratic-forces%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Over%20700%20delegates%20from%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20country%2C%20representing%20people%E2%80%99s%20movements%2C%20trade%20unions%20and%20civil%20society%20organisations%2C%20had%20gathered%20for%20the%20event.%20The%20Delhi%20Police%20did%20not%20allow%20the%20final%20day%20of%20the%20summit%20to%20take%20place.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A28%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwe20-summit-issues-declaration-calling-for-solidarity-unity-among-democratic-forces%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Safeguarding%20Academic%20Freedom%20Is%20the%20Bedrock%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Constitutional%20Morality%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F20162709%2Fashoka-bckgd.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20attempt%20to%20initiate%20a%20discussion%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98new%E2%80%99%20foundations%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%2C%20chief%20economic%20advisor%20to%20the%20prime%20minister%20Bibek%20Debroy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fopinion%2Fonline-views%2Ftheres-a-case-for-we-the-people-to-embrace-a-new-constitution-11692021963182.html%5C%22%3Ewrote%20a%20column%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20Independence%20Day%2C%20arguing%20the%20following%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%202023%2C%2073%20years%20after%201950.%20Our%20current%20Constitution%20is%20largely%20based%20on%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20Act%20of%201935.%20In%20that%20sense%2C%20it%20is%20also%20a%20colonial%20legacy.%20In%202002%2C%20there%20was%20a%20report%20by%20a%20commission%20set%20up%20to%20review%20the%20working%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20but%20it%20was%20a%20half-hearted%20effort.%20As%20with%20many%20aspects%20of%20law%20reform%2C%20a%20tweak%20here%20and%20another%20there%20won%E2%80%99t%20do.%20We%20should%20start%20with%20first%20principles%2C%20as%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20debates.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWhat%20Constitution%20does%20India%20need%20for%202047%3F%20Much%20else%20follows.%20How%20many%20states%20do%20we%20need%3F%20In%20similar%20vein%2C%20what%20about%20the%20Seventh%20Schedule%20and%20local%20bodies%3F%20If%20development%20is%20correlated%20with%20urbanization%2C%20why%20have%20we%20set%20up%20these%20rural-urban%20silos%2C%20exemplified%20in%20the%2073rd%20and%2074th%20amendments%3F%20But%20what%E2%80%99s%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20role%20and%20how%20much%20supervisory%20control%20does%20it%20have%20over%20high%20courts%3F%20Little%2C%20if%20we%20go%20by%20the%20Constitution.%20What%20about%20judicial%20appointments%3F%20What%20about%20the%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20role%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20might%20feel%20these%20are%20valid%2C%20critical%20questions%20to%20reflect%20upon%20as%20India%20is%20apparently%20%E2%80%98shining%E2%80%99%20when%20viewed%20from%20the%20corridors%20of%20power.%20Still%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20founding%20constitution%20involved%20constituent%20assembly%20debates%20for%20a%20period%20of%20three%20years.%20This%20gave%20space%20for%20critical%20dialogue%2C%20open%20access%2C%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20to%20raise%2Fdiscuss%20complex%20issues.%20What%20came%20out%20of%20it%2C%20under%20Dr%20B.R.%20Ambredkar%E2%80%99s%20anchorship%20and%20prowess%2C%20was%20a%20carefully%20crafted%20constitution%20addressing%20the%20concerns%20of%20a%20deeply-stratified%2C%20heterogenous%20socio-economic%20fabric%20in%20a%20newly%20born%20republic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20we%20now%20see%20is%20of%20course%20a%20different%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20constitutionally%20safeguarded%20rights%2C%20entitlements%20and%20freedoms%20are%20bulldozed%20with%20less%20regard%20for%20reflection%2C%20or%20critical%20discourse%2C%20any%20attempts%20to%20%E2%80%98recreate%20a%20new%20Constitution%E2%80%99%20may%20only%20appear%20to%20be%20loose%20talk%20or%20an%20insidious%20attempt%2C%20as%20part%20of%20a%20government-supported%20rhetorical%20exercise%20for%20gathering%20attention%20towards%20another%20majoritarian%20intervention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFreedoms%20are%20the%20bedrock%20of%20constitutional%20liberalism.%20A%20good%20marker%20of%20ascertaining%20the%20role%2C%20value%20and%20realisation%20of%20%E2%80%98freedoms%E2%80%99%20remains%20an%20integral%20process%20of%20securing%20%3Cem%3Evikas%20%3C%2Fem%3Eor%20development%20for%20all%2C%20and%2C%20in%20Nobel%20laureate%20Amartya%20Sen%E2%80%99s%20words%2C%20is%20closely%20linked%20with%20a%20gradual%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ucl.ac.uk%2Fdpu-projects%2F21st_Century%2Ffreedom%2FRemoving_Unfreedoms.pdf%5C%22%3Eremoval%20of%20%E2%80%98unfreedoms%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20(poverty%2C%20malnutrition%2C%20unemployment%2C%20subjugation%20of%20rights%2C%20protective%20security%20etc.).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20redefined%20%3Cem%3Efreedom-%3C%2Fem%3Ebased%20approach%20to%20development%20describes%20processes%20of%20development%20as%20a%20quest%20by%20individuals%20(citizens)%20for%20ever%20expanding%20freedoms.%20Hitherto%2C%20economistic%20criteria%20for%20evaluating%20development%20consisted%20of%20measuring%20Gross%20National%20Product%2C%20personal%20incomes%2C%20levels%20of%20industrialisation%2C%20technological%20advances%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Democracy%20Needs%20Dissenters%2C%20Critical%20Thinkers.%20But%20IISc%20Row%20Reveals%20Eroding%20Academic%20Freedom.%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Facademic-freedom-iisc-democracy-india%5C%22%3EDemocracy%20Needs%20Dissenters%2C%20Critical%20Thinkers.%20But%20IISc%20Row%20Reveals%20Eroding%20Academic%20Freedom.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20these%20continue%20to%20remain%20valid%20for%20evaluation%20of%20economic%20progress%2C%20they%20are%20now%20seen%20only%20as%20a%20%3Cem%3Emeans%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20expand%20freedom%20and%20not%20as%20%3Cem%3Eends%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20goal%20of%20development%20becomes%20the%20pursuit%20of%20enabling%20ever-expanding%20freedoms%20to%20be%20gained%20and%20this%20becomes%20the%20overarching%20objective%20of%20human%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20context%20of%20%3Cem%3Efreedoms%3C%2Fem%3E%20being%20instrumental%20to%20development%20of%20any%20given%20nation%20also%20means%20that%20a%20nation%E2%80%99s%20knowledge%20infrastructure%20%E2%80%93%20anchored%20by%20its%20academic%20landscape%2Feducation%20system%20across%20all%20forms%20(from%20lower%20to%20higher%20academia)%20%E2%80%93%20must%20be%20able%20to%20remain%20free%2C%20to%20practice%20and%20nurture%20%3Cem%3Ecritique%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20as%20a%20practice%20of%20its%20own%2C%20is%20the%20basic%20means%20to%20incubating%20critical%20reflection%20in%20a%20parliamentary%20democracy%20for%20a%20polished%2C%20consensus%20driven%20outcome%20to%20be%20produced%20on%20complex%20issues.%20Issues%20that%20are%20also%20of%20the%20kind%20raised%20by%20Debroy%20in%20his%20column.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20when%20there%20is%20no%20free%20space%20left%20for%20either%20critique%2C%20dissent%20or%20critical%20reflection%2C%20we%20are%20coerced%20to%20operate%20and%20function%20in%20an%20era%20of%20darkness%20where%20even%20the%20only%20source%20of%20light%20is%20controlled%20by%20a%20usurper%20of%20power.%20The%20current%20regime%E2%80%99s%20actions%20reflect%20that%20%E2%80%93%20a%20usurper%E2%80%99s%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fauthor%2F310387%2Fdeepanshu-mohan%5C%22%3Ethe%20nature%20of%20events%20unfolding%20at%20National%20Capital%20Region%E2%80%99s%20elite%20private%20Ashoka%20University%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20a%20bastion%20of%20%E2%80%98liberal%E2%80%99%20arts%20education%2C%20shows%20how%20an%20environment%20of%20unfreedoms%20(not%20freedoms)%20is%20shaping%20the%20academic%20culture%20of%20higher%20education%2C%20even%20in%20private%20%E2%80%98elite%E2%80%99%20institutions%20where%20government%20support%2Fmoney%20isn%E2%80%99t%20dictating%20the%20working%20affairs.%20Students%20of%20such%20institutions%20almost%20pay%20to%20%E2%80%98buy%E2%80%99%20liberty%20and%20learn%20%E2%80%98liberal%20education%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20best%20kind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBack%20in%202021%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fnarendra-modi-academic-freedom-universities-webinars-7184744%2F%5C%22%3Ein%20a%20column%20written%20for%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Sudheendra%20Kulkarni%20observed%20how%20the%20Modi%20government%20had%20then%20mounted%20its%20biggest%20attack%20on%20%E2%80%98academic%20freedom%E2%80%99%20with%20its%20(new)%20diktat%20on%20organising%20international%20webinars%2Fconferences%2Fworkshops.%20The%20mini%20%E2%80%9Csurgical%20strike%E2%80%9D%20came%20in%20the%20form%20of%20an%20%E2%80%9Coffice%20memorandum%E2%80%9D%20on%20January%2015%2C%202021%20from%20the%20offices%20of%20an%20undersecretary%2C%20the%20junior-most%20bureaucrat%20in%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Education%2C%20and%20was%20innocuously%20titled%20%E2%80%98Revised%20Guidelines%20for%20holding%20online%2Fvirtual%20Conferences%2C%20Seminars%2C%20Training%2C%20etc.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20new%20guidelines%2C%20all%20%E2%80%9Ccentral%20educational%20institutions%2C%20publicly-funded%20universities%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20this%20category%20will%20naturally%20include%20affiliated%20colleges%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cand%20organisations%20owned%20and%20controlled%20by%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20%2F%20State%20Government%E2%80%9D%20were%20required%20to%20get%20prior%20approval%20from%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20if%20they%20want%20to%20hold%20online%20international%20conferences%20or%20seminars%20on%20subjects%20related%20to%20%E2%80%9Csecurity%20of%20State%2C%20Border%2C%20Northeast%20states%2C%20UT%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20Ladakh%20or%20any%20other%20issues%20which%20are%20clearly%2Fpurely%20related%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20internal%20matter%2Fs%E2%80%9D.%20Furthermore%2C%20they%20need%20approval%20from%20the%20appropriate%20%E2%80%9Cadministrative%20secretary%20for%20the%20event%20as%20well%20as%20for%20the%20list%20of%20participants%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20just%20one%20instance%20amongst%20the%20many%20measures%20taken%20by%20the%20current%20regime%20in%20its%20last%20nine%20years%20of%20power%20that%20was%20aimed%20at%20curtailing%20the%20%3Cem%3Eacademic%20freedom%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20public%20institutions.%20The%20wreckage%20and%20damage%20caused%20to%20%E2%80%98free%E2%80%99%20thinking%20critical%20academic%20discourse%20from%20social%20sciences%20to%20other%20disciplines%20has%20now%20seen%20almost%20every%20public%20institution%20toeing%20the%20government%20line.%20And%20then%20came%20the%20turn%20of%20private%20institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Campuses%20of%20Foreign%20Universities%20in%20India%20Will%20Be%20a%20Tool%20in%20the%20Hands%20of%20Hindu%20Nationalists%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feducation%2Fhindu-nationalists-foreign-campus-india%5C%22%3ECampuses%20of%20Foreign%20Universities%20in%20India%20Will%20Be%20a%20Tool%20in%20the%20Hands%20of%20Hindu%20Nationalists%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EObserve%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiaforum.in%2Farticle%2Facademic-freedom-india%5C%22%3Ethe%20shape%20decline%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Academic%20Freedom%20Index%20developed%20by%20the%20V-Dem%20Institute%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Gothenburg.%20The%20components%20of%20academic%20freedom%20are%20well%20defined%20and%20are%20broadly%20the%20same%20across%20countries%20by%20the%20institute%20(irrespective%20of%20what%20one%20might%20say%20about%20its%20methodology).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiaforum.in%2Farticle%2Facademic-freedom-india%5C%22%3EAcademic%20Freedom%20Index%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Eis%20coded%20on%20the%20following%20indicators%3A%201)%20freedom%20to%20research%20and%20teach%3B%20(2)%20freedom%20of%20academic%20exchange%20and%20dissemination%3B%20(3)%20institutional%20autonomy%3B%20(4)%20campus%20integrity%3B%20and%20(5)%20freedom%20of%20academic%20and%20cultural%20expression.%20While%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiaforum.in%2Farticle%2Facademic-freedom-india%5C%22%3Ethis%20%3Cem%3EIndia%20Forum%3C%2Fem%3E%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%20follows%20the%20same%20parameters%2C%20their%20authors%2C%20Nandini%20Sundar%20and%20Gawhar%20Fazili%2C%20follow%20a%20somewhat%20different%20order%20and%20emphasis%2C%20drawing%20on%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epw.in%2Fjournal%2F2018%2F24%2Fspecial-articles%2Facademic-freedom-and-indian-universities.html%5C%22%3Eprevious%20research%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Eon%20the%20Indian%20context.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiaforum.in%2Farticle%2Facademic-freedom-india%5C%22%3Ewords%20of%20the%20authors%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9CUniversities%20for%20their%20part%20must%20restore%20and%20strengthen%20conventions%20on%20institutional%20autonomy%3B%20and%20inform%20student%20and%20faculty%20unions%20of%20their%20rights%20to%20academic%20freedom%20and%20free%20speech.%20Contracts%20with%20faculty%20should%20include%20a%20clause%20on%20the%20protection%20of%20academic%20freedom%2C%20i.e.%2C%20they%20will%20not%20be%20penalized%20for%20extra-mural%20activities.%20Faculty%20should%20create%20a%20network%20to%20support%20academics%20(faculty%20and%20students)%20at%20risk.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20seems%C2%A0%20the%20administration%20and%20governing%20body%20of%20an%20elite%20institution%20like%20Ashoka%20failed%20to%20ensure%20these%20basic%20tenets%20of%20%E2%80%98academic%20freedom%E2%80%99.%20While%20Ashoka%20University%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fauthor%2F310387%2Fdeepanshu-mohan%5C%22%3Eadministrative%20response%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Sabyasachi%20Das%E2%80%99s%20paper%20leading%20to%20his%20resignation%20may%20have%20evoked%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fanother-ashoka-professor-pulapre-balakrishnan-quits-over-research-paper-faculty-writes-support-letter-4302608%5C%22%3Esolidarity%20amongst%20faculty%20members%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.the-edict.in%2Fpost%2Feconomics-department-announces-boycott-of-classes-english-and-creative-writing-follow-suit%5C%22%3Eand%20students%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20campus%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fauthor%2F310387%2Fdeepanshu-mohan%5C%22%3Eaction%20taken%20by%20the%20governing%20body%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20academic%20administration%20is%20symptomatically%20in%20alignment%20with%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20in%20every%20academic%20institution%20in%20India%20right%20now%20%E2%80%93%20and%20is%20extremely%20worrying.%20More%20private%20institutions%20may%20follow%20suite%20and%20faculty%20members%20may%20be%20more%20explicitly%20shunted%20out%20for%20pursuing%20critical%20thought.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20the%20possibility%20of%20this%20seen%20coming%3F%20Or%20perhaps%20the%20%E2%80%98elite%E2%80%99%20only%20roars%20in%20dissent%20when%20its%20own%20position%2C%20people%2C%20freedoms%20and%20interests%20are%20threatened%2C%20without%20caring%2C%20nor%20engaging%20in%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20outside%20the%20boundaries%20of%20its%2Ftheir%20own%20gated%20communities.%20Elite%2C%20private%20institutions%20need%20to%20be%20forewarned%20about%20their%20own%20vulnerability%20to%20the%20current%20atmosphere%20of%20instilled%20fear%2C%20conformism%20and%20subjugating%20of%20democratic%20principles.%20It%20is%20the%20safeguarding%20and%20practice%20of%20these%20principles%20that%20make%20well-written%2Fdrafted%20constitutions%20work%20for%20their%20people%20and%20their%20welfare.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDebroy%2C%20as%20prolific%20a%20writer%20and%20scholar%20as%20he%20is%2C%20must%20be%20aware%20of%20the%20conditions%20in%20which%20the%20socio-political%2C%20economic%20landscape%20of%20a%20regime%E2%80%99s%20nefarious%20actions%20%E2%80%93%20and%20attack%20on%20academic%20freedom%20%E2%80%93%20makes%20any%20reasonable%20dialogue%20on%20some%20of%20the%20most%20complex%20yet%20fundamental%20building%20block%20questions%20of%20the%20Constitution%20a%20precarious%20challenge%20%E2%80%93%20no%20matter%20what%20the%20future%20stakes%20might%20be%20for%202047%20or%20the%20next%201%2C000%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fdeepanshu-mohan%5C%22%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20an%20associate%20professor%20and%20director%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20at%20O.P.%20Jindal%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692529098000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F20162709%2Fashoka-bckgd.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fsafeguarding-academic-freedom-is-the-bedrock-of-indias-constitutional-morality%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Any%20attempt%20to%20reimagine%20or%20recreate%20a%20constitution%20may%20fall%20woefully%20short%20in%20its%20objective%20if%20%E2%80%98freedoms%E2%80%99%20are%20threatened%